Percent.name: Percent
Percent.description: An integer that is in the range of a percent value.

snCamProfile.name: snCamProfile
snCamProfile.description: This object identifies CAM partition profile. Each profile adjusts the partitions to optimize the device for corresponding applications.

snCamUsageL3Table.name: snCamUsageL3Table
snCamUsageL3Table.description: A list of snCamUsageL3 entries. This table contains information of the entity's CAM usage for layer 3 traffic.

snCamUsageL3Entry.name: snCamUsageL3Entry
snCamUsageL3Entry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to CAM usage for layer 3 traffic

snCamUsageL3Slot.name: snCamUsageL3Slot
snCamUsageL3Slot.description: A number which uniquely identifies a linecard in the device

snCamUsageL3Processor.name: snCamUsageL3Processor
snCamUsageL3Processor.description: A number which uniquely identifies the network processor within a linecard in the device

snCamUsageL3Type.name: snCamUsageL3Type
snCamUsageL3Type.description: This object identifies the type of layer 3 traffic passing through the network processor.

snCamUsageL3Supernet.name: snCamUsageL3Supernet
snCamUsageL3Supernet.description: This object identifies the Supernet for the layer 3 type traffic. It provides information for longest match lookup. For example, zero indicates all the bits of IP address will be matched, and one indicates all but the lowest bit in IP address will be matched. The range is [0..32] for IPv4 and IPv4VPN, where a value of 32 indicates the entry is the total of other supernets indexed by [0..31]. The range is [0..10] for IPv6, where a value of 10 indicates the entry is the total of other supernets indexed by [0..9].

snCamUsageL3Size.name: snCamUsageL3Size
snCamUsageL3Size.description: The effective CAM size for this layer 3 traffic entry. For ipv4 traffic, each unit is 4 bytes. For ipv4vpn, each unit is 8 bytes. For ipv6, each unit is 16 bytes.

snCamUsageL3Free.name: snCamUsageL3Free
snCamUsageL3Free.description: The amount of CAM currently available for this layer 3 traffic entry. For ipv4 traffic, each unit is 4 bytes. For ipv4vpn, each unit is 8 bytes. For ipv6, each unit is 16 bytes.

snCamUsageL3UsedPercent.name: snCamUsageL3UsedPercent
snCamUsageL3UsedPercent.description: The percentage of CAM currently being used for this layer 3 traffic entry.

snCamUsageL2Table.name: snCamUsageL2Table
snCamUsageL2Table.description: A list of snCamUsageL2 entries. This table contains information of the entity's CAM usage for layer 2 traffic.

snCamUsageL2Entry.name: snCamUsageL2Entry
snCamUsageL2Entry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to CAM usage for layer 2 traffic

snCamUsageL2Slot.name: snCamUsageL2Slot
snCamUsageL2Slot.description: A number which uniquely identifies a linecard in the device

snCamUsageL2Processor.name: snCamUsageL2Processor
snCamUsageL2Processor.description: A number which uniquely identifies the network processor within a linecard in the device

snCamUsageL2Type.name: snCamUsageL2Type
snCamUsageL2Type.description: This object identifies the type of layer 2 traffic passing through the network processor.

snCamUsageL2Size.name: snCamUsageL2Size
snCamUsageL2Size.description: The effective CAM size for this layer 2 traffic entry. Each unit is 8 bytes.

snCamUsageL2Free.name: snCamUsageL2Free
snCamUsageL2Free.description: The amount of CAM currently available for this layer 2 traffic entry. Each unit is 8 bytes.

snCamUsageL2UsedPercent.name: snCamUsageL2UsedPercent
snCamUsageL2UsedPercent.description: The percentage of CAM currently being used for this layer 2 traffic entry.

snCamUsageSessionTable.name: snCamUsageSessionTable
snCamUsageSessionTable.description: A list of snCamUsageSession entries. This table contains information of the entitiy's CAM usage for sessions.

snCamUsageSessionEntry.name: snCamUsageSessionEntry
snCamUsageSessionEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to CAM usage for sessions.

snCamUsageSessionSlot.name: snCamUsageSessionSlot
snCamUsageSessionSlot.description: A number which uniquely identifies a linecard in the device

snCamUsageSessionProcessor.name: snCamUsageSessionProcessor
snCamUsageSessionProcessor.description: A number which uniquely identifies the network processor within a linecard in the device

snCamUsageSessionType.name: snCamUsageSessionType
snCamUsageSessionType.description: This object identifies the type of sessions.

snCamUsageSessionSize.name: snCamUsageSessionSize
snCamUsageSessionSize.description: The effective CAM size for this session traffic entry. For IPv4 sessions, each unit is 16 bytes. For IPv4 sessions, each unit is 64 bytes.

snCamUsageSessionFree.name: snCamUsageSessionFree
snCamUsageSessionFree.description: The amount of CAM currently available this session traffic entry. For IPv4 sessions, each unit is 16 bytes. For IPv4 sessions, each unit is 64 bytes.

snCamUsageSessionUsedPercent.name: snCamUsageSessionUsedPercent
snCamUsageSessionUsedPercent.description: The percentage of CAM currently being used by this session traffic entry

snCamUsageOtherTable.name: snCamUsageOtherTable
snCamUsageOtherTable.description: A list of snCamUsageOther entries. This table contains information of the entitiy's CAM usage for types other than L3, L2, or Session.

snCamUsageOtherEntry.name: snCamUsageOtherEntry
snCamUsageOtherEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to CAM usage for types other than L3, L2, or Session

snCamUsageOtherSlot.name: snCamUsageOtherSlot
snCamUsageOtherSlot.description: A number which uniquely identifies a linecard in the device

snCamUsageOtherProcessor.name: snCamUsageOtherProcessor
snCamUsageOtherProcessor.description: A number which uniquely identifies the network processor within a linecard in the device

snCamUsageOtherSize.name: snCamUsageOtherSize
snCamUsageOtherSize.description: The effective CAM size for this Other traffic entry. For GRE, each unit is 8 bytes. For multicast VPLS, each unit is 16 bytes.

snCamUsageOtherFree.name: snCamUsageOtherFree
snCamUsageOtherFree.description: The amount of CAM currently available this Other traffic entry. For GRE, each unit is 8 bytes. For multicast VPLS, each unit is 16 bytes.

snCamUsageOtherUsedPercent.name: snCamUsageOtherUsedPercent
snCamUsageOtherUsedPercent.description: The percentage of CAM currently being used by this entry
